records.addlTxt: Justice Point noncompliance Report forwarded to judge for review and filed.

Defendant Quinetta Tashi Hall appeared by video.  Attorney Lori Ann Kuehn appeared by video for Quinetta Tashi Hall.  Attorney Jessica Ann Behling appeared by video for State of Wisconsin. 
Parties are requesting a court date with the co-defendant's case.  Case is adjourned to 11-11-22 at 1:30 pm for status by zoom.
This hearing may be streamed live on DAcast at the discretion of the Court:
https://iframe.dacast.com/live/4dafbf46-ed15-c11c-fa22-a58262833632/d84cd54a-763c-3a58-15a9-b84acf306616
Status conference scheduled for November 11, 2022 at 01:30 pm.

CASE HEARD IN PRELIM FOR BR. 10:
Defendant Quinetta Tashi Hall appeared by video.  Attorney Lori Ann Kuehn in court for Quinetta Tashi Hall.  Prosecuting attorney Jessica Ann Behling appeared by video for the State of Wisconsin. 
Preliminary hearing proceeded.  Sworn for the State: MPD Officer S. Zolo.  State rests.  Defense rests.  Defense motion to dismiss argued and denied. Court found probable cause and bound defendant over for trial.  Original information received and filed;  defendant given a copy, waived reading, was arraigned in open court and plead not guilty. Ms Hall is reminded to continue working with Justice Point.  Case is adjourned to Branch 10.
Scheduling conference scheduled for October 14, 2022 at 08:30 am.

CASE HEARD IN PRELIM FOR BR 10
Defendant Quinetta Tashi Hall in court, appear in person.  Abby Rockendorf appeared in person for the State of Wisconsin.  
Case set for a preliminary hearing. State witness present. SPD has not appointed counsel. Court ordered case adjourned for CAUSE for a Preliminary Hearing in Preliminary Hearing Court, Room 146 of the Criminal Justice Facility.  Preliminary hearing scheduled for September 8, 2022 at 08:30 am.
OSPD Appointment of Counsel Report, filed.

Defendant Quinetta Tashi Hall in court in person. Gregg Herman appeared by video for the State of Wisconsin.  
Case in court for preliminary hearing. States witness is present. OPD needs additional time to appoint an attorney. State requests that the matter be set for a State V. Lee hearing or status; denied. Court finds good CAUSE to adjourn preliminary hearing.  Preliminary hearing scheduled for August 5, 2022 at 08:30 am.
E-mail to Katleen Attewell from Kim Paige filed for Court consideration .
Received and filed. Justice Point Supervision Report. Deputy Court Clerk: EAB.

Court ordered no contact with CMR (5/26/09),; QDR (8/26/10),; CPR (6/26/13),; MJD (4/14/17),; and/or KDD (9/19/18).;
No Contact Order, signed and filed.
Court ordered defendant TURNED OVER TO Justice Point for SUPERVISION Level 3.

Defendant Quinetta Tashi Hall in court with attorney Dawn Marie Rablin.  Defendant Quinetta Tashi Hall in custody.  James C Griffin appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Quinetta Tashi Hall appeared by video means with Attorney.  Defendant is advised this case is assigned to Judge Havas, Branch 10.  Defendant given a copy of the complaint and advised of maximum penalties, right to counsel and right to a preliminary hearing.  Court reviewed the complaint and found probable cause to hold the defendant for further proceedings.  DEFENDANT IS INDIGENT AND PUBLIC DEFENDER WILL PROVIDE COUNSEL. Commissioner advised DNA sample has been obtained from the Defendant.  Court advised Defendant she may qualify to have the DNA sample data expunged if she meets the conditions under Wisconsin Statutes Section 165.77(4). Defense enters a plea of NOT GUILTY as to misdemeanor count(s) 9, 10, and 11.   
This hearing will be streamed live on Dacast:  https://iframe.dacast.com/live/4dafbf46-ed15-c11c-fa22-a58262833632/99073afd-37c2-acfa-830d-b1ddcaebf0ea  Preliminary hearing scheduled for July 13, 2022 at 01:30 pm.
Defendant in Custody, Court appearance today in Intake Court, Room 137A.
